At this time, the cpp grammer does not allow the usage of macros as part of the &#39;#include&#39; statement. It must be &#39;&quot;path.h&quot;&#39; or &#39;&lt;path.h&gt;&#39;. The &quot;stringifaction&quot; operators (both &#39;#&#39; and &#39;##&#39;) are not processed for pre-processor directives (line starting with &#39;#&#39;)
